{{Refimprove|date=May 2009}} {{Infobox person | name = Carrie Fletcher | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = Carrie Hope Fletcher | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1992|10|22}} | birth_place = [[South Harrow]], [[London, England]] | death_date = <!--{{death date and age|1992|10|22|yyyy|yy|yy}}--> | death_place = | othername = | website = | spouse = }}{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2010}} '''Carrie Hope Fletcher''' (born 22 October 1992) is a former child [[actress]] who was born in [[South Harrow]], [[London, England]]. Carrie is the younger sister of [[Tom Fletcher]], the founding member of the British pop/rock band ''[[McFly (band)|McFly]]''.<ref>{{IMDB name|2886817}}</ref>
==Career== She has played in numerous London stage shows and television productions. Most notably she played Jemima Potts in the London run of ''[[Chitty Chitty Bang Bang (musical)|Chitty Chitty Bang Bang]]'', the [[West End theatre|West End]] musical, and can be heard on the original cast CD recording. She was also in the original cast of a second [[Sherman Brothers]] musical, ''[[Mary Poppins (musical)|Mary Poppins]]''. She previously attended Northwood College Independent Day School for Girls, and is an accomplished [[Painting|painter]]. She also plays [[piano]], [[guitar]] and [[saxophone]] and writes her own music, stating that her main influences are [[Tom Fletcher]], [[McFly]], [[Avril Lavigne]], [[Fall Out Boy]], [[My Chemical Romance]], [[Elliot Minor]] and [[Plain White T's]] and [[Paramore]] .{{Citation needed|date=January 2008}}
